description: From Middle English misreden, from Old English misrǣdan (“to advise wrongly; read wrongly”), equivalent to mis- +‎ read. Cognate with Saterland Frisian misräide (“to go wrong, fail”), Dutch misraden (“to guess wrongly”), German missraten (“to fail; go wrong; become wayward”). For the noun, compare Old English misrǣd (“misguidance; misconduct”).

verbs.description: misread (third-person singular simple present misreads, present participle misreading, simple past and past participle misread)

entries.meaning: To read wrongly; misconstrue; misinterpret; mistake the sense or significance of.
